        "title": "Nightly release pipeline hardened with retries and gh-pages recovery",
        "summary": "A sustained pass on the nightly pipeline made asset pruning, changelog history sync, and gh-pages publishing far more resilient, and improved how proof screenshots get framed.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Replaced the inline asset-prune step in the nightly workflow with a dedicated retrying script that tolerates transient GitHub API errors, and added a new workflow that mirrors published changelog media into dated history entries on gh-pages.",
